./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1778:sdp/verification/frac-0072-verify.md:24:The three end-to-end tests drive `resolve_harmonic_plan()` through a deterministic live-like keyboard input (MIDI notes 67/71/74, garden `F lydian`, inner `Dm`, sustained pedal), assert `G:lydian` authority resolution, verify that section functions/cadences/progressions/chord-degree triads/harmonic functions/transition intents are fully populated and internally consistent, confirm modulation continuity via `common_tones()` / `pivot_degree()`, align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` output against the resolved plan, assert tension ordering (emergence < bridge, afterglow < bridge), and round-trip the full payload through `ScoreTree.to_json()` / `ScoreTree.from_dict()`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1792:sdp/verification/t-032@20260425t183959z-verify.md:18:The file placement and naming follow the established `senseweave` patterns. The use of `.writeDefFile("synthdefs/")` is consistent with other SynthDefs in the project. The Lead agent noted a convention for sampler-related voices where binaries are generated at runtime on the target host (`cypherclaw`), which explains the absence of the `.scsyndef` file in the repo.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1794:sdp/verification/t-032@20260425t183959z-verify.md:32:The implementation is excellent. The static tests are a great addition given the environment constraints. Note that while the `sw_sampler.scsyndef` was not committed, it must be verified on `cypherclaw` using the provided `test_sw_sampler.scd` once deployed.
