./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3506:- Added depth-2 run_agent Ollama end-to-end test coverage (frac-0098): `tests/test_ollama_run_agent.py` now includes `OllamaRunAgentEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.run_agent` Ollama HTTP path through one happy lifecycle: `_invoke_ollama` is called once with the prompt, timeout, task category, and task label, the cloud subprocess invoker is fenced off, the pet manager records `start`/`end`/`idle` for `ollama` with a finite duration, the observatory records exactly one `gate_pass=True` task result alongside the `semaphore_acquired`/`semaphore_released` pair with no healing events, and the combined diagnostic round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_ollama_run_agent_depth.py` pins the run_agent test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `run_agent` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4590 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3514:- Added depth-2 narrative API health end-to-end test coverage (frac-0094): `tests/test_narrative_api_health.py` now includes `NarrativeApiHealthEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `/health` HTTP surface through one cold healthy probe (auth-token-configured app, all checkers true, version `0.1.0`, world-store `list_events` probe call), one warm healthy probe (monotonic uptime, second probe call), one degraded probe (world store raises, ollama checker false, narrative engine importable), and a JSON-safe combined diagnostic round trip. `tests/test_test_narrative_api_health_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `cypherclaw.narrative_api.app` health behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4582 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3516:- Added depth-2 narrative API entity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0093): `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` now includes `NarrativeApiEntitiesEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing world-entity HTTP surface through Deniable character creation, multi-operation property mutation, get-by-ID round trip, Deniable-visible shared/entity listing, and JSON-safe diagnostic serialization. `tests/test_test_narrative_api_entities_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `cypherclaw.narrative_api` entity behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4580 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3526:- Added depth-2 midi-state end-to-end test coverage (frac-0088): `tests/test_midi_state.py` now includes `MidiStateEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `MidiState` public surface in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/midi_state.py` through a realistic chord-with-controllers session (chord on, sustain pedal, mod wheel, expression, volume, pitch bend, velocity-zero release, explicit `note_off`), confirms live tracker state, and verifies the `to_dict()` snapshot is JSON-safe with a sorted `notes_on` list, round-trips through `json.dumps`/`json.loads` and `MidiState.from_dict(...)`, and stays consistent with the `note_to_name`/`name_to_note` helpers for the played chord. `tests/test_test_midi_state_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `MidiState` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path tracker output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4566 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
