./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3594:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3602:- Added depth-2 image API schema summaries (frac-0050): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/schemas.py` now exposes `TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES`, `ACTIVE_JOB_STATUSES`, frozen `JobLifecycleSummary` and `InternalSpecProfile` dataclasses, and typed helpers `is_terminal_status`, `build_job_lifecycle_summary`, `summarize_status_response`, `build_internal_spec_profile`, and `summarize_internal_spec`. The helpers give operator logs and dashboards JSON-safe lifecycle/spec metadata including terminal-state classification, output counts, error flags, image dimensions, pixel count, megapixels, prompt previews, style presence, model overrides, and content-piece IDs without changing any Pydantic request/response fields or runtime behavior. `tests/test_image_api_schemas_depth.py` pins the new helper surface and fractal depth >= 2; existing parser, worker, app, jobs DB, S3 uploader, startup identity, and narrative ASGI startup anchors remain green.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3604:- Added depth-2 image API S3 uploader reports (frac-0049): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/s3_uploader.py` now exposes module-level `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL`, `DEFAULT_CONTENT_TYPE`, and `CONTENT_TYPE_BY_EXTENSION` constants plus a frozen `UploadReport` dataclass and typed helpers `guess_content_type`, `categorize_upload_size`, `build_upload_report`, `summarize_upload`, and `summarize_upload_report` so worker batches and operator dashboards can map filenames to canonical MIME types, aggregate `UploadResult` records into bucket / object-count / total-bytes / keys / urls reports, classify byte sizes into empty/small/medium/large bands, and emit JSON-safe per-result and per-batch summaries. `upload_image` keeps its keyword-only signature, single `put_object` call, and direct-S3 URL contract; the cache-control header is now sourced from `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL` rather than a literal. `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py` pins MIME classification (known + unknown + missing suffix), batch aggregation, empty-iterable handling, size-band thresholds, JSON-safe summaries, the cache-header contract, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py` remains the regression anchor for existing upload behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3622:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw model diagnostics (frac-0039): `promptclaw/models.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigModelReport` plus typed helpers `sorted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, `config_model_report`, `summarize_config_model`, `summarize_route_decision`, and `summarize_run_state` so config, route, agent, and run dataclasses can emit deterministic JSON-safe operator summaries without changing existing dataclass fields or orchestration call sites. The narrative ASGI entry point `cypherclaw.narrative_api.main:app` now calls `bootstrap_identity()` before app creation, matching the `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api` startup path so first boots mint and persist identity automatically. `tests/test_promptclaw_models_depth.py` pins model summary counts, sorted JSON-safe output, route/run summaries, an end-to-end orchestrator run summary, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py` now pins ASGI import identity persistence between boots, while existing config/router/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3628:- Added depth-2 Theramini MIDI listener (frac-0036): `my-claw/tools/theramini_midi.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `midi_to_freq`, `midi_to_name`, `parse_midi_messages`, `apply_midi_event`, `process_buffer`, `render_state`, `write_state`, `read_midi_buffer`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus frozen `MidiEvent` and mutable `MidiState` dataclasses that hold the current note, last-note timestamp, silence-start timestamp, CC map, and pitch-bend value. The listener parses raw Note On / Note Off / CC / pitch-bend bytes (including the velocity-zero Note On = Note Off and 2-byte program/channel-pressure cases), folds events into a per-cycle `MidiState`, and atomically writes `/tmp/theramini_state.json` with the existing consumer contract (`timestamp`, `is_playing`, `pitch_hz`, `pitch_note`, `pitch_confidence`, `state`, `consecutive_silence_ms`, `midi_cc`, `pitch_bend`) after passing through `senseweave.theramini_duet.normalize_theramini_state` so the duet conversation contract is preserved. `is_playing` decays to `False` after `2.0` seconds without a fresh note. Loop control gains `--device`, `--interval`, `--state-path`, `--once`, and `--max-iterations`; missing or unopenable MIDI devices fall back to the existing `state="no_device"` payload shape. `tests/test_theramini_midi.py` pins import safety, MIDI parse/apply, active-note and silent-window rendering, end-to-end fd writes, and the no-device fallback; `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`, `tests/test_theramini_duet.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3632:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3668:- Added depth-2 lung capacity report helpers (frac-0016): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` now exposes frozen `LaneBreathStat` and `LungCapacityReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_breath_stat`, `analyze_lung_capacity`, and `summarize_lung_capacity_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R11 rule once and read back per-lane breath outcomes (lane name, voice, role, resolved capacity seconds, inserted vs. tagged breath counts, and an `applies` flag for role-gated wind/voice lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `LungCapacityRule.apply`, `apply_lung_capacity`, and `lung_capacity_seconds_for_voice` semantics are preserved so MIDI/Theramini/score-tree callers and `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py` pins inserted-vs-tagged counting, non-wind lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3674:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:3682:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
