./CHANGELOG.md:669:- Added depth-2 sw_sampler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0116): `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now includes `SwSamplerEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef source and the SC-side runtime harness `my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts every documented SynthDef control default (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms=80.0`, `density=12.0`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate>=1`, `out_bus=0`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send=0.4`), verifies the integrated granular signal-chain order (`Impulse.kr` -> `TRand.kr` -> `.midiratio` -> `Sweep.ar`/`Phasor.ar` -> `GrainBuf.ar(... bufnum ...)` -> `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` -> dry `Out.ar(out_bus, ...)` -> parallel `Out.ar(fx_bus, ...)` send) on a comment-stripped source, confirms the dry write to `out_bus` is not scaled by `fx_send` so the parallel-send architecture is preserved, inspects the SC-side runtime harness for source compile, 2-second render, non-silence, FFT spectral peak, gate=0 release tail, and known-content buffer allocation, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic of the SynthDef name, source path, runtime-harness path, defaults, signal-chain stages, stage positions, and runtime checks through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the SCD source and SC-side harness already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4669 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:733:- Added depth-2 midi-state end-to-end test coverage (frac-0088): `tests/test_midi_state.py` now includes `MidiStateEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `MidiState` public surface in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/midi_state.py` through a realistic chord-with-controllers session (chord on, sustain pedal, mod wheel, expression, volume, pitch bend, velocity-zero release, explicit `note_off`), confirms live tracker state, and verifies the `to_dict()` snapshot is JSON-safe with a sorted `notes_on` list, round-trips through `json.dumps`/`json.loads` and `MidiState.from_dict(...)`, and stays consistent with the `note_to_name`/`name_to_note` helpers for the played chord. `tests/test_test_midi_state_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `MidiState` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path tracker output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4566 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:835:- Added depth-2 Theramini MIDI listener (frac-0036): `my-claw/tools/theramini_midi.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `midi_to_freq`, `midi_to_name`, `parse_midi_messages`, `apply_midi_event`, `process_buffer`, `render_state`, `write_state`, `read_midi_buffer`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus frozen `MidiEvent` and mutable `MidiState` dataclasses that hold the current note, last-note timestamp, silence-start timestamp, CC map, and pitch-bend value. The listener parses raw Note On / Note Off / CC / pitch-bend bytes (including the velocity-zero Note On = Note Off and 2-byte program/channel-pressure cases), folds events into a per-cycle `MidiState`, and atomically writes `/tmp/theramini_state.json` with the existing consumer contract (`timestamp`, `is_playing`, `pitch_hz`, `pitch_note`, `pitch_confidence`, `state`, `consecutive_silence_ms`, `midi_cc`, `pitch_bend`) after passing through `senseweave.theramini_duet.normalize_theramini_state` so the duet conversation contract is preserved. `is_playing` decays to `False` after `2.0` seconds without a fresh note. Loop control gains `--device`, `--interval`, `--state-path`, `--once`, and `--max-iterations`; missing or unopenable MIDI devices fall back to the existing `state="no_device"` payload shape. `tests/test_theramini_midi.py` pins import safety, MIDI parse/apply, active-note and silent-window rendering, end-to-end fd writes, and the no-device fallback; `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`, `tests/test_theramini_duet.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:875:- Added depth-2 lung capacity report helpers (frac-0016): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` now exposes frozen `LaneBreathStat` and `LungCapacityReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_breath_stat`, `analyze_lung_capacity`, and `summarize_lung_capacity_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R11 rule once and read back per-lane breath outcomes (lane name, voice, role, resolved capacity seconds, inserted vs. tagged breath counts, and an `applies` flag for role-gated wind/voice lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `LungCapacityRule.apply`, `apply_lung_capacity`, and `lung_capacity_seconds_for_voice` semantics are preserved so MIDI/Theramini/score-tree callers and `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py` pins inserted-vs-tagged counting, non-wind lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
./CHANGELOG.md:881:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:889:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:949:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
./CHANGELOG.md:967:- Added SuperCollider recipe references for curriculum: created 22 discoverable recipe files in `my-claw/curriculum/recipes/supercollider/` for topics from MIDI-to-frequency to master-bus, linked them from EMSD-102 and EMSD-130 reference docs, and added static validation tests in `tests/test_supercollider_recipes.py` that check for required labels without coupling to the live audio server.
./CHANGELOG.md:1066:- Added a mode-aware harmonic planner and live keyboard-grimoire path: tracker solo now preserves major/minor/modal key specs, ignores stale garden and MIDI files, supports scene-level modulation, and `midi_keyboard_listener.py` discovers the real keyboard devices while publishing pedal-derived harmonic suggestions.
