CHANGELOG.md:794:- Added depth-2 coherence-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0065): `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` now ships a new `TestCoherenceEngineEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public `CoherenceEngine` and `NullCoherenceEngine` surface through complete end-to-end paths. The new tests walk every hook in canonical order (`pre_routing → post_routing → pre_lead → post_lead → pre_verify → post_verify → finalize`) and verify event types, phases, monotonic sequence numbers, run-id propagation, and SQLite persistence across an engine rebuild; write a `constitution.json` with one HARD and one SOFT keyword rule and confirm `EnforcementMode.FULL` blocks `post_routing`/`post_lead`/`post_verify` while `EnforcementMode.MONITOR` records the same violations without blocking, propagating HARD severity, both rule ids, and a negative trust delta on `post_lead`; record two architectural decisions through `record_decision` and confirm `pre_routing`/`pre_lead`/`pre_verify` inject the `## Active Decisions` block with at least one matching title; step the graduation manager across three `finalize` calls plus alternating `record_graduation_observation` outcomes and verify the run/observation/true-/false-positive counters and stable enforcement mode; round-trip a full replayed event payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys and verify each event's `sequence_number`, `run_id`, and dict `payload`; and loop `NullCoherenceEngine` across multiple run ids confirming every hook returns an approved verdict with empty violations and empty injected context plus an empty replay. `tests/test_test_coherence_engine_depth.py` pins `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestCoherenceEngine` and `TestNullCoherenceEngine` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/engine.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4421 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:796:- Added depth-2 local-client end-to-end test coverage (frac-0064): `tests/test_client_local.py` now includes `TestLocalAdaClientEndToEnd`, which drives the existing `LocalAdaClient` public surface through typed `GenerationRequest` and legacy mapping paths. The new tests verify typed requests produce real mono WAV previews with stable local request ids, protocol summaries, zero-cost metadata, expected latency from an injected clock, valid WAV container metadata, nonzero frames, and passing `validate_generation_result` outcomes; verify mapping requests return queue/cache/storage-ready payloads with `prediction_id`, `api_request_id`, `request_id`, `audio_path`, `sample_rate`, duration, model, cost, per-second cost, and nonnegative latency; round-trip request summaries and combined diagnostics through `json.dumps`; and confirm repeated mapping generation reuses the same deterministic path and bytes. `tests/test_test_client_local_depth.py` pins `tests/test_client_local.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing local-client assertions and production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4414 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:798:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:800:- Added depth-2 capstone-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0062): `tests/test_capstone_engine.py` now includes `TestCapstoneCycleEndToEnd`, which drives the existing public `build_capstone_cycle()` API through complete EMSD capstone planning paths. The new tests verify all five canonical phases expose linked family, patch, arc, palette, mix, sampling, and DSP contracts; assert occupied Theramini routing activates the Conversation dialogue path and ducking behavior; assert away-practice late phases retarget sampling and DSP focus to `self_bus`; compare quiet cadences against occupied cycles for lower density and quieter mix targets; verify repertoire songs shape identity families, patches, imagery, and statement text; and round-trip phase diagnostics through `json.dumps`. `tests/test_capstone_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 9 real functions versus 2 trivial). Existing capstone assertions and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/capstone_engine.py` source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4401 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:802:- Added depth-2 breath-to-filter end-to-end test coverage (frac-0061): `tests/test_breath_to_filter.py` now ships a `TestBreathToFilterEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public breath-to-filter API (`estimate_breath_rate`, `breath_phase`, `breath_to_filter_params`, `breath_to_visual_params`) through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests sweep multiple sine-breath BPMs (3, 6, 12) end-to-end through rate estimation, phase extraction, and filter/visual parameter derivation; assert the documented neutral output for flat and empty RMS histories; sweep a phase table (0.0–1.0) to verify cutoff peaks at inhale (0.25) and troughs at exhale (0.75), resonance peaks at extremes (0.0/0.5), and visual scale/brightness mirror the breath wave; check the documented `min(rate/15, 1.0)` mix-saturation curve across rate steps from 0 to 30 BPM; round-trip filter and visual outputs through `json.dumps`; render JSON-safe diagnostics across calm/fast/flat/noisy signal types; verify rate-detection tolerance per BPM, deterministic pipeline output, and a spot-check of the cosine cutoff curve at known phase extremes. `tests/test_breath_to_filter_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 26 real functions versus 24 trivial). Existing breath-to-filter assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/breath_to_filter.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (4392 tests, 3 skipped, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:804:- Added depth-2 audio-analysis end-to-end test coverage (frac-0060): `tests/test_audio_analysis.py` now includes `TestAudioAnalysisEndToEnd`, which drives the existing pure `audio_analysis` public API through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests analyze tonal sine signals through amplitude, autocorrelation pitch, note/key mapping, content classification, and spectral peak extraction; classify deterministic speech-like dynamic material; retain a sparse impulse through click-transient detection and transient classification; derive silence/onset/sustain/release transitions from windowed RMS values; and confirm public outputs can be serialized into JSON-safe diagnostics. `tests/test_audio_analysis_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 21 trivial functions versus 24 real). Existing audio-analysis assertions and `my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:806:- Added depth-2 artist-identity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0059): `tests/test_artist_identity.py` now ships a `TestArtistIdentityEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public artist-identity surface (`select_mode`, `apply_mode_to_commission`, `next_tonal_choice`, `MODES`, `MODES_BY_NAME`, `HOME_TONAL_MAP`, `VOICE_ROLES`, `SIGNATURE_VOICES`) through looped, table-driven end-to-end methods. The new tests sweep every `ArtistMode` for required commission metadata keys, tempo-band membership across many seeds, voice-count propagation, silence/restraint/harmony field propagation, sampler-density propagation, voice/groove/modal CSV serialization, the `mode_avoid_attention_pullers` string contract, deterministic application across non-zero seeds, input-dict immutability, JSON round-trip safety, and preservation of pre-existing commission keys; verify the entire `HOME_TONAL_MAP` (only `B` is home, `D` and `F#` are the unique distance-1 neighbors, every distance is a non-negative int); walk the documented `select_mode` priority matrix including the inclusive 0.6 STORM threshold, screen-active gating that requires `presence='present'`, equivalent evening/night routing, and a full presence/time/severity/screen sweep that always returns a known mode; sweep `next_tonal_choice` across many seeds for every mode confirming roots stay in `HOME_TONAL_MAP` and scales stay in `mode.preferred_modes`, determinism per (mode, seed), and that modulation-willingness correlates with venturing (SOLITARY <= COMPANION <= STORM); and run the end-to-end `select -> apply -> choose` pipeline across a presence/time/screen matrix with JSON-safe payloads. `tests/test_artist_identity_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing artist-identity assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
