CHANGELOG.md:814:- Added depth-2 end-to-end accompaniment test coverage (frac-0055): `tests/test_accompaniment.py` now ships a new `TestAccompanimentEndToEnd` class that drives the existing Korsakov accompaniment public surface (`DensityTracker`, `select_accompaniment_type`, `breathing_swell`, `should_transition_gradually`, `should_pedal`, `pedal_note`, `get_pattern`, and the six pattern generators) through end-to-end multi-step pytest methods. The new tests sweep the documented density bands and verify the inverse-density rule, iterate every pattern type 1-6 to assert non-empty events with positive amps/releases, sweep `breathing_swell` over rest/active/edge inputs, walk full phrase boundaries through `should_pedal` + `pedal_note`, run the dense-melody and resting-melody pipelines end-to-end through a synthetic `DensityTracker` window, and pin a six-bar composer loop. A `test_test_accompaniment_reaches_depth_two` gate test asserts the file's fractal classification is at least depth 2. Existing `TestDensityTracker`, `TestSelectAccompanimentType`, `TestPatterns`, `TestPedalPoint`, `TestBreathing`, and `TestTransition` assertions are preserved unchanged; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:816:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:818:- Added depth-2 test_genai smoke probe (frac-0053): root-level `test_genai.py` is now a typed module exposing a frozen `GenAIProbeResult` dataclass plus `create_genai_client`, `list_model_names`, `probe_genai_client`, `summarize_probe_result`, `format_probe_lines`, and `main` so callers, tests, and operator dashboards can drive `probe → summarize → render → main` without re-implementing the conditional script logic. The success path returns a populated result with the sampled model names; any raised `Exception` is folded into an `ok=False` result with the stringified error and zero models. `summarize_probe_result` is JSON-safe (`sampled_models` rendered as a list); `format_probe_lines` preserves the original CLI output format byte-for-byte ("Successfully created client without explicit API key." header plus per-model lines on success, single "Error: <error>" line on failure); `main()` runs the probe and prints each line, returning exit code 0 to match the original `python test_genai.py` smoke behavior. `tests/test_test_genai_depth.py` pins the new probe surface, client construction (explicit key + default-auth env), limit-respecting model sampling, success/error result paths, JSON-safe summary, canonical CLI line rendering, end-to-end main, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:820:- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:822:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw memory journal helpers (frac-0051): `promptclaw/memory.py` now exposes a frozen `MemoryEntry` dataclass plus typed helpers `format_run_block`, `parse_memory_log`, and `summarize_memory_log`, and `MemoryStore` gains `entries`, `latest_entry`, and `summary` read-side methods so callers and operator diagnostics can render a single run's memory block, parse the project memory file back into structured entries (run id, title, status, lead, verifier, final phase, body), and emit a JSON-safe aggregate (entry count, latest run id, sorted status counts, sorted lead-agent counts excluding the `n/a` placeholder). `MemoryStore.append_run_summary` now delegates block rendering to `format_run_block` so the on-disk markdown shape stays byte-identical for orchestrator clarification-pause and final-summary writes. `tests/test_promptclaw_memory_depth.py` pins canonical block layout, `n/a` agent fallbacks, append/parse round-trip, empty-input handling, JSON-safe summary aggregation, `n/a` lead exclusion, store read helpers (including missing-file path), and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` remains the regression anchor for end-to-end run behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
